  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2014-05-06", 
    "text": "Directs the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) to revise regulations to require an issuer to furnish investors with additional specified disclosures regarding compensatory benefit plans if the aggregate sales price or amount of securities sold during any consecutive 12-month period exceeds $20 million (currently $5 million).\n\nDirects the SEC to index that aggregate sales price or amount for inflation every 5 years."
  }, 
